The paper deals with searching in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of adaptive algorithms and analysis of error rates suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves graph theory and analysis of algorithms, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.GT). The use of amortized analysis and probabilistic models suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves bounds and analysis of algorithms, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
